1
00:00:53,512 --> 00:00:57,015
YUMI'S CELLS 3

2
00:00:57,099 --> 00:01:02,020
EPISODE 7
LOW POWER MODE HUMAN

3
00:01:23,834 --> 00:01:27,713
AHN DAE-YONG, KIM JU-HO

4
00:01:34,011 --> 00:01:35,637
ANDERSON

5
00:01:42,811 --> 00:01:45,522
- Go back, go back! Go back!
- Hurry, hurry! Hurry!

6
00:01:45,606 --> 00:01:48,817
It seems there are two types of people.

7
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:53,405
The type that gets energized
when they're with people

8
00:01:54,323 --> 00:01:57,701
and the type whose energy drains
in a crowded place...

9
00:01:57,951 --> 00:01:58,952
Like me.

10
00:01:59,536 --> 00:02:02,414
See? I told you they could do it.

11
00:02:02,581 --> 00:02:04,499
Hey, did you see that?
Did you see the speed?

12
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:05,959
Yes, I saw it.

13
00:02:06,043 --> 00:02:08,712
- Wasn't that amazing?
- It was amazing.

14
00:02:11,381 --> 00:02:13,175
Get a hit!

15
00:02:15,344 --> 00:02:17,929
Get up, Shin PD. Do it with us.

16
00:02:18,013 --> 00:02:20,432
Shout!

17
00:02:20,515 --> 00:02:22,809
Get a hit!

18
00:02:22,893 --> 00:02:25,646
- Get a hit!
- Go, go!

19
00:02:25,729 --> 00:02:28,106
- A home run is fine too!
- How?

20
00:02:28,190 --> 00:02:31,860
- Hit a satisfying one for us
- Hit a satisfying one for us

21
00:02:31,943 --> 00:02:34,863
- Get a hit
- A hit!

22
00:02:34,946 --> 00:02:37,240
Get a hit!

23
00:02:37,949 --> 00:02:39,743
The producer called, so...

24
00:02:40,202 --> 00:02:43,705
Hit a satisfying one for us

25
00:02:43,789 --> 00:02:46,249
Right now!

26
00:02:50,671 --> 00:02:51,713
Yes, yes.

27
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:55,050
Then I'll check again and send it to you.

28
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:56,843
Okay.

29
00:03:02,474 --> 00:03:05,227
If I weren't the editor for a writer
who writes baseball novels

30
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:07,354
I would have no reason to come here.

31
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:29,251
To reduce energy loss

32
00:03:29,751 --> 00:03:32,504
I live in Low Power Mode
when I'm outside my house.

33
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:39,052
That's why during the day

34
00:03:39,928 --> 00:03:41,346
only Rational Cell works.

35
00:03:44,558 --> 00:03:45,642
Look at that.

36
00:03:46,101 --> 00:03:48,603
When did all those flowers bloom?

37
00:03:48,812 --> 00:03:52,274
- They really did.
- Gosh, the weather is so nice.

38
00:03:52,774 --> 00:03:54,693
It makes me want to go out and have fun.

39
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:55,902
I know.

40
00:03:56,737 --> 00:03:58,947
Should we ditch work and run off?

41
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,240
- Really?
- Really?

42
00:04:02,743 --> 00:04:04,786
No, of course not.

43
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:07,289
What was that?

44
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:20,635
Rational Cell isn't sentimental,
so it gets work done quickly.

45
00:04:21,762 --> 00:04:22,763
On top of that...

46
00:04:23,472 --> 00:04:27,058
- Would you like another drink?
- No, I'm fine.

47
00:04:29,603 --> 00:04:32,731
- I was given these chocolates.
- Well.

48
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:34,191
I'll be leaving now.

49
00:04:36,401 --> 00:04:38,487
- Okay.
- It's good at refusing offers.

50
00:04:44,785 --> 00:04:47,496
And it reduces energy consumption
by drawing boundaries.

51
00:04:47,913 --> 00:04:51,333
Our calm and rational Soon-rok.
I like you.

52
00:04:58,006 --> 00:05:01,927
People think of that as
being calm and rational.

53
00:05:04,888 --> 00:05:06,556
- Three-pitch strikeout!
- Three-pitch strikeout!

54
00:05:08,183 --> 00:05:09,434
- Three-pitch strikeout!
- Chief Editor Ahn.

55
00:05:09,518 --> 00:05:10,936
- Mr. Kim.
- Here you go.

56
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:13,104
- Three-pitch strikeout!
- Three-pitch strikeout!

57
00:05:14,606 --> 00:05:17,859
Three-pitch strikeout! Strikeout!

58
00:05:17,943 --> 00:05:19,444
They should keep going like this.

59
00:05:19,528 --> 00:05:22,030
- Three-pitch strikeout!
- However

60
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:26,993
all the cells are inactive
outside the house.

61
00:05:29,746 --> 00:05:32,457
- Here, help yourself.
- Hey, thanks.

62
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,711
- This crab looks great, right?
- My mouth is watering.

63
00:05:36,795 --> 00:05:40,257
Eat a lot.
Although I'm not the one paying.

64
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,384
No, eat a lot.
Eating is the only thing that lasts.

65
00:05:42,592 --> 00:05:43,593
What else is there to life?

66
00:05:45,804 --> 00:05:48,890
- I can't even taste what I'm eating.
- Oh, right.

67
00:05:49,057 --> 00:05:51,101
You know the movie
Attack on Bats is out, right?

68
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:52,727
- Who wants to go? Hands up!
- Me! Me!

69
00:05:52,811 --> 00:05:53,979
- Let's go!
- I've been wanting to see that.

70
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:56,147
We have to go! We have to go. Yeah.

71
00:05:57,148 --> 00:05:58,859
I'm sorry, but I...

72
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:01,027
Shin PD. You're coming, right?

73
00:06:01,653 --> 00:06:03,905
- Well...
- If Shin PD won't go, I'm not going.

74
00:06:04,239 --> 00:06:06,199
- I'm not going.
- Come on, Shin PD.

75
00:06:06,283 --> 00:06:07,742
- What's with you guys?
- I'm not going.

76
00:06:07,826 --> 00:06:09,578
- Let's go together!
- Shin PD!

77
00:06:09,661 --> 00:06:11,997
- Come on, the producer has to go!
- Shin PD! Shin PD!

78
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:13,874
- Shin PD!
- Shin PD!

79
00:06:21,756 --> 00:06:23,592
You're no longer needed here.

80
00:06:24,426 --> 00:06:26,678
Does Sung-hee always work on herself?

81
00:06:26,761 --> 00:06:30,432
She thinks she's capable of solving
everything on her own, does she?

82
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,267
What a conceited egotist.

83
00:06:32,434 --> 00:06:34,019
She's a typical Korean.

84
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:35,729
A workaholic...

85
00:06:38,189 --> 00:06:41,359
Ouch! The popcorn's spilling.

86
00:06:41,443 --> 00:06:42,444
Goodness!

87
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:47,407
Please leave a message after the tone.

88
00:07:04,424 --> 00:07:06,801
Using your phone is so rude.

89
00:07:15,894 --> 00:07:18,772
I can't even focus on the movie.

90
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:23,193
Hey, I wonder if it's too late.
Oh, here he comes, here he comes.

91
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:25,153
This movie was longer than I thought.

92
00:07:26,863 --> 00:07:29,074
- I'll be going now.
- Bye!

93
00:07:29,157 --> 00:07:32,410
- Get home safe, Shin PD!
- Don't tell them you were with us.

94
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:42,170
Hello.

95
00:07:42,545 --> 00:07:45,215
On top of that, I'm in a rush.

96
00:07:49,678 --> 00:07:50,971
Door closing.

97
00:08:00,146 --> 00:08:01,147
Hello.

98
00:08:01,564 --> 00:08:02,732
- Hello.
- In a team that's still unfamiliar...

99
00:08:02,816 --> 00:08:04,609
I'm sorry. I'm a little late.

100
00:08:04,693 --> 00:08:07,862
And an animal shows up...

101
00:08:12,784 --> 00:08:16,162
Shin PD, do you have anything to say?

102
00:08:25,797 --> 00:08:27,007
I'm in big trouble.

103
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:29,009
I can't focus on the script.

104
00:08:31,094 --> 00:08:35,015
How can a person in love be calm?

105
00:08:39,728 --> 00:08:41,563
I'm sorry, but what are you talking about?

106
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:45,316
"How can a person in love be calm?"

107
00:08:47,318 --> 00:08:49,988
What does love have to do with being calm?

108
00:08:59,581 --> 00:09:02,876
Maltese. Right.
Let's just talk about the Maltese.

109
00:09:03,084 --> 00:09:05,211
You don't need to understand the Maltese.

110
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:08,923
But Maltese dogs aren't very smart.

111
00:09:09,924 --> 00:09:11,342
Maltese dogs have low intelligence?

112
00:09:11,634 --> 00:09:14,095
- I thought they were smart.
- Their intelligence isn't high.

113
00:09:14,679 --> 00:09:15,889
Yes, that's it.

114
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:17,557
Way to go, Soon-rok.

115
00:09:17,932 --> 00:09:20,226
Let's use the Maltese
to get through this crisis.

116
00:09:23,021 --> 00:09:25,315
When I'm in a bad mood,
she stays quiet next to me

117
00:09:25,398 --> 00:09:26,983
and when I'm happy, she knows it
like magic and brings me a ball.

118
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:29,069
And she barks when her owner video calls.

119
00:09:29,152 --> 00:09:30,487
How smart is that?

120
00:09:30,612 --> 00:09:32,614
Isn't that something all dogs do?

121
00:09:33,031 --> 00:09:34,407
Unless they're a lizard?

122
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:39,287
Right. That dog and lizard
example was good.

123
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:52,425
Going down.

124
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:53,843
Good work today.

125
00:09:54,052 --> 00:09:56,137
- You worked hard.
- You got this.

126
00:09:57,639 --> 00:09:59,432
- Koko, bye!
- Koko, bye!

127
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:01,351
- The doors are closing.
- Bye.

128
00:10:06,689 --> 00:10:09,901
By the way, don't you think
Ms. Kim was a little offended?

129
00:10:10,401 --> 00:10:13,655
- Why?
- Shin PD said Maltese are dumb.

130
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:15,657
She seemed a little upset.

131
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:20,203
I said the Maltese was dumb, not her.
Why would she be offended?

132
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:23,581
- Still, from a pet owner's view...
- But it's not even her dog.

133
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:25,834
Still, it's a matter of feelings.

134
00:10:27,001 --> 00:10:28,628
Ah, Shin PD is so cold.

135
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:30,421
You're just too rational.

136
00:10:33,925 --> 00:10:35,468
What are you talking about?

137
00:10:35,552 --> 00:10:40,306
Ms. Yu-mi isn't a Maltese,
nor is she a Maltese owner

138
00:10:40,557 --> 00:10:42,809
so why would she be offended?

139
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:44,310
Goodness.

140
00:10:45,895 --> 00:10:47,605
I just don't get it...

141
00:11:07,417 --> 00:11:10,670
A day like today is too much.

142
00:11:11,254 --> 00:11:14,507
I worked all day by myself.

143
00:11:15,717 --> 00:11:16,759
Yeah, I know.

144
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:18,803
But it's okay.

145
00:11:19,721 --> 00:11:21,014
Because I'm home now.

146
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:20,323
Because I'm...

147
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:25,411
a complete homebody.

148
00:12:42,303 --> 00:12:44,639
It's always a struggle
when you leave home.

149
00:12:45,265 --> 00:12:47,308
Home is the best.

150
00:12:54,107 --> 00:12:56,484
All my senses only awaken
when I'm at home.

151
00:13:10,498 --> 00:13:11,541
Perfect.

152
00:13:15,670 --> 00:13:17,130
My sense of taste awakens.

153
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:21,592
My sense of hearing awakens.

154
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:38,818
That's it!

155
00:13:39,402 --> 00:13:40,570
Good eye.

156
00:13:41,112 --> 00:13:42,155
Bases loaded!

157
00:13:48,119 --> 00:13:50,038
Baseball is best when you watch it on TV.

158
00:14:04,344 --> 00:14:05,887
Is he dead?

159
00:14:18,733 --> 00:14:22,320
And movies are best watched
from the front row of your room.

160
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:29,410
At home, my emotion is at its peak

161
00:14:30,119 --> 00:14:33,956
so I can read the writer's intentions
between the lines.

162
00:14:34,332 --> 00:14:35,333
Then...

163
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:37,001
"Did he leave his phone?"

164
00:14:37,085 --> 00:14:38,711
The phone rang

165
00:14:39,879 --> 00:14:42,340
and Seon-ju's gaze turned toward it.

166
00:14:43,508 --> 00:14:45,343
Whose call could it be?

167
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:49,514
It was that forgotten name, Eun-young.

168
00:14:51,307 --> 00:14:53,851
Seon-ju realized in that moment.

169
00:14:54,685 --> 00:14:56,521
How calm she was.

170
00:14:57,772 --> 00:15:00,400
MISSED CALL
YU DA-EUN (INTERN)

171
00:15:09,659 --> 00:15:10,660
(Go back in)

172
00:15:28,469 --> 00:15:29,846
How can a person in love...

173
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:32,765
be so calm?

174
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:44,986
The Maltese wasn't the important thing.

175
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:49,490
Ms. Kim, this is Shin Soon-rok.

176
00:15:50,199 --> 00:15:51,993
I'm sending you additional feedback.

177
00:16:11,762 --> 00:16:13,598
A homebody's night is always too short.

178
00:16:17,894 --> 00:16:19,854
The worst thing for such homebodies...

179
00:16:25,693 --> 00:16:26,819
JANG SU-HYE PD

180
00:16:28,654 --> 00:16:31,574
- Hello?
- Sorry, Soon-rok. Are you home?

181
00:16:32,033 --> 00:16:34,202
- Nothing special going on today?
- No.

182
00:16:35,495 --> 00:16:36,537
But why?

183
00:16:40,458 --> 00:16:41,501
Right now?

184
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,003
...is a day like today.

185
00:16:45,922 --> 00:16:48,174
A sudden weekend business trip.

186
00:16:48,257 --> 00:16:49,258
Okay, I understand.

187
00:16:50,301 --> 00:16:52,303
Jeez, what the heck?

188
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:55,473
But it's Saturday.

189
00:17:20,665 --> 00:17:23,042
There's no time. Let's just go.

190
00:17:41,185 --> 00:17:42,228
Hello.

191
00:17:54,574 --> 00:17:56,075
SEOUL, BUSAN

192
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:03,124
My glasses.

193
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:06,377
You forgot your glasses too?

194
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:14,594
Oh, no. I'm already drained,
and it's only morning.

195
00:18:14,677 --> 00:18:16,679
What am I going to do today?

196
00:18:34,071 --> 00:18:35,114
I'm sorry.

197
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:07,229
Are you going with the writer
looking like this?

198
00:19:07,605 --> 00:19:09,523
You didn't even wash your face.

199
00:19:10,483 --> 00:19:11,942
What about your image?

200
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:27,291
This is great.
I was getting bored of going alone.

201
00:19:28,209 --> 00:19:29,251
Have a seat.

202
00:19:30,378 --> 00:19:33,005
- Let's definitely sit apart.
- It's all right.

203
00:19:33,339 --> 00:19:34,590
My seat is over there.

204
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:52,358
You don't even know the trip schedule yet.

205
00:19:52,858 --> 00:19:55,778
I'm a mess, and I don't have my glasses.

206
00:19:56,153 --> 00:19:59,365
Gosh, today is the worst.

207
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:02,159
Yes, I received the materials
for the Book Talk.

208
00:20:02,243 --> 00:20:05,454
But I don't have the contact details
for the person in charge.

209
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:08,040
Yes, thank you. Bye.

210
00:20:08,124 --> 00:20:11,419
Wait, I'm sorry. And the car...

211
00:20:12,169 --> 00:20:14,588
It's a rental car. Got it.

212
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:22,847
I'm just going to sit
next to you for a second.

213
00:20:23,556 --> 00:20:24,598
What's going on?

214
00:20:24,682 --> 00:20:26,517
Ms. Yu-mi is saying something.

215
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:29,186
Let's talk, Shin PD.

216
00:20:29,478 --> 00:20:31,147
Are you unhappy working with me?

217
00:20:33,149 --> 00:20:35,609
What? What did she say?

218
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:39,864
Ouch. What did she just say?

219
00:20:40,698 --> 00:20:43,826
What does she mean
if you're unhappy working with her?

220
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:46,787
I'm not sure what she means either.

221
00:20:47,121 --> 00:20:48,956
Could you tell me specifically?

222
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:50,833
I think I need to hear it.

223
00:20:56,213 --> 00:20:58,299
What does she want to hear?

224
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:00,593
Specifically?

225
00:21:00,801 --> 00:21:02,219
What is she talking about?

226
00:21:02,928 --> 00:21:04,847
Is Ms. Yu-mi angry right now?

227
00:21:05,514 --> 00:21:06,682
Why would she be angry?

228
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:09,268
She just brought me a drink a moment ago.

229
00:21:09,351 --> 00:21:11,145
Why is she acting like this
all of a sudden?

230
00:21:15,316 --> 00:21:16,317
Huh?

231
00:21:18,068 --> 00:21:22,198
- I don't understand what you mean...
- I want to know the real reason.

232
00:21:22,573 --> 00:21:24,074
The reason you're leaving our team.

233
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:27,203
Didn't the Chief Editor tell you?

234
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:29,413
- Our schedules kept clashing-
- That's an excuse.

235
00:21:30,372 --> 00:21:31,373
An excuse?

236
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:34,001
Shin PD.

237
00:21:34,168 --> 00:21:36,587
I've been patient for long enough, okay?

238
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:39,507
I don't usually get this worked up

239
00:21:39,590 --> 00:21:41,675
but I've been so irritated lately.

240
00:21:46,806 --> 00:21:49,683
What? I think something's gone very wrong.

241
00:21:52,186 --> 00:21:54,480
Everyone! Wake up, all of you!

242
00:21:54,563 --> 00:21:57,191
This is an emergency!

243
00:22:01,946 --> 00:22:03,155
Oh no!

244
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:06,909
We're in big trouble.

245
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:09,286
Soon-rok has run out of battery.

246
00:22:10,204 --> 00:22:11,247
Shin PD?

247
00:22:36,063 --> 00:22:39,149
EPISODE 8
BOLT OUT OF THE BLUE

248
00:22:51,036 --> 00:22:52,329
Shin PD?

249
00:23:10,723 --> 00:23:11,724
He's smiling.

250
00:23:12,349 --> 00:23:14,268
He's smiling right now, isn't he?

251
00:23:14,518 --> 00:23:16,854
Why is he smiling? Yu-mi is being serious.

252
00:23:16,937 --> 00:23:20,107
Are you kidding? I said to answer.
So why the hell are you smiling!

253
00:23:24,612 --> 00:23:27,197
Yu-mi revealed her true feelings.

254
00:23:29,491 --> 00:23:32,328
So why won't you say anything, you jerk!

255
00:23:34,455 --> 00:23:36,957
What's this? Not a cloud in the sky,
but all of a sudden?

256
00:24:00,773 --> 00:24:01,815
Why...

257
00:24:03,651 --> 00:24:06,612
Shin PD, why are you smiling...

258
00:24:08,364 --> 00:24:10,074
JANG SU-HYE PD

259
00:24:12,076 --> 00:24:14,328
I'm sorry. It's an urgent call.

260
00:24:19,416 --> 00:24:20,459
Yes, hello?

261
00:24:20,918 --> 00:24:24,672
Yes, we'll arrive in an hour.

262
00:24:25,965 --> 00:24:29,385
No, we should stop by the hotel first.

263
00:24:29,969 --> 00:24:30,970
And...

264
00:24:32,304 --> 00:24:33,305
Sorry?

265
00:24:39,019 --> 00:24:42,773
This stop is Singyeongju,
Singyeongju Station.

266
00:24:43,899 --> 00:24:46,443
Please exit after the train has come
to a complete stop...

267
00:24:46,527 --> 00:24:49,071
Was that schedule shared
with the Chief Editor as well?

268
00:24:49,905 --> 00:24:53,701
I think he thinks
it's the 12 o'clock train.

269
00:24:55,369 --> 00:24:59,581
Okay, then I'll check again
and get back to you.

270
00:24:59,665 --> 00:25:01,667
- Okay, bye.
- The doors are opening.

271
00:25:05,504 --> 00:25:06,547
Yes, PD.

272
00:25:07,631 --> 00:25:09,383
Yes, about tomorrow's event.

273
00:25:10,092 --> 00:25:12,052
Yes, right.

274
00:25:13,762 --> 00:25:16,181
Yes, I heard a little about it,
but what kind of video...

275
00:25:26,233 --> 00:25:27,276
What?

276
00:25:31,739 --> 00:25:32,781
What the...

277
00:25:36,785 --> 00:25:38,704
What is with this guy, seriously?

278
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,918
What? What was that?

279
00:25:45,002 --> 00:25:46,003
I don't know.

280
00:25:46,253 --> 00:25:48,672
Why is this happening out of the blue?

281
00:25:48,756 --> 00:25:51,258
Guys, I'm getting anxious.

282
00:25:51,341 --> 00:25:54,595
Could it be Hysterius?

283
00:25:55,888 --> 00:25:56,972
HYSTERIUS

284
00:26:00,142 --> 00:26:02,811
Hysterius is in the cryo-base.

285
00:26:02,895 --> 00:26:07,149
Don't you think he woke up
because he got so mad at Soon-rok?

286
00:26:07,232 --> 00:26:11,070
That's it. Hysterius has woken up.

287
00:26:12,404 --> 00:26:13,447
Let's go see.

288
00:26:18,702 --> 00:26:21,330
He just subtly smiled,
took a call, and left.

289
00:26:21,955 --> 00:26:23,207
His methods are quite...

290
00:26:23,999 --> 00:26:25,542
Not a chance, buddy.

291
00:26:25,793 --> 00:26:27,961
I'm going to hear everything
and confront you.

292
00:26:28,212 --> 00:26:29,838
- What time should I send it by?
- The doors are closing.

293
00:26:31,340 --> 00:26:32,382
Okay.

294
00:26:36,053 --> 00:26:37,679
The train is now departing.

295
00:26:47,606 --> 00:26:49,650
- Hello?
- Oh, I see.

296
00:26:50,109 --> 00:26:51,902
- If you send the video,
- Hello?

297
00:26:51,985 --> 00:26:53,654
- I'll watch it, and then decide...
- Hello?

298
00:26:54,404 --> 00:26:56,031
Okay, thank you.

299
00:26:56,365 --> 00:26:57,908
- Okay, okay, I understand.
- Excuse me!

300
00:26:57,991 --> 00:26:59,034
- Bye.
- Hello?

301
00:27:00,285 --> 00:27:01,286
Hey!

302
00:27:06,625 --> 00:27:09,878
- What in the world...
- Ms. Kim.

303
00:27:11,296 --> 00:27:12,339
Ms...

304
00:27:13,507 --> 00:27:14,550
Why did you...

305
00:27:21,557 --> 00:27:24,351
This is a disaster.
You even missed the train?

306
00:27:24,601 --> 00:27:26,603
I'm doomed!

307
00:27:26,687 --> 00:27:32,651
THE KTX FOR BUSAN HAS DEPARTED

308
00:27:37,781 --> 00:27:38,824
I mean, what the...

309
00:27:39,741 --> 00:27:40,784
What kind of...

310
00:27:42,035 --> 00:27:43,120
What...

311
00:27:43,704 --> 00:27:46,790
Did he really miss the train?
This is absurd.

312
00:27:47,082 --> 00:27:48,542
Did he do that on purpose?

313
00:27:48,625 --> 00:27:53,005
- Because he wanted to avoid Yu-mi?
- Hey! You son of a bitch!

314
00:27:59,511 --> 00:28:00,762
Ms. Kim, I'm sorry.

315
00:28:00,846 --> 00:28:02,556
I missed the train
while I was on the phone.

316
00:28:03,515 --> 00:28:05,475
I'll take the next train right away.

317
00:28:05,726 --> 00:28:09,021
- I'm sorry.
- I'm honestly speechless.

318
00:28:09,396 --> 00:28:10,898
All right.

319
00:28:10,981 --> 00:28:13,483
I'll grab your luggage and get off.

320
00:28:15,319 --> 00:28:16,361
Thank you.

321
00:28:18,989 --> 00:28:21,909
This guy is unbelievable, huh?

322
00:28:27,581 --> 00:28:28,749
Oh, seriously.

323
00:28:34,671 --> 00:28:36,006
Hey, Fishing Cell.

324
00:28:37,257 --> 00:28:41,053
- Are you going home already?
- Yeah, but I'm empty-handed today.

325
00:28:41,345 --> 00:28:42,387
Why?

326
00:28:42,471 --> 00:28:44,806
But today was the day
Yu-mi was the most pissed off.

327
00:28:46,475 --> 00:28:47,935
You didn't catch any Angerfish?

328
00:28:48,185 --> 00:28:50,312
There were a lot of Angerfish.

329
00:28:50,854 --> 00:28:53,482
There really were a lot today.

330
00:28:57,861 --> 00:29:02,491
Wow, I bet I'll get a full catch today.

331
00:29:25,889 --> 00:29:27,599
They were killed by lightning?

332
00:29:27,808 --> 00:29:29,434
Yeah, in an instant.

333
00:29:29,810 --> 00:29:33,355
Wait, if all the Angerfish died...

334
00:29:45,659 --> 00:29:48,537
That means Yu-mi's anger disappeared.

335
00:29:49,079 --> 00:29:51,999
But Yu-mi was totally pissed off.

336
00:30:17,065 --> 00:30:19,359
Hysterius probably got out...

337
00:30:21,486 --> 00:30:22,487
Oh, he's here.

338
00:30:22,779 --> 00:30:26,616
- Hysterius is sleeping?
- Then what was it?

339
00:30:27,159 --> 00:30:30,537
That's strange. Sudden lightning
is a first for Yu-mi's Village.

340
00:30:33,373 --> 00:30:37,878
Is this strange weather happening
because Yu-mi is getting older?

341
00:30:38,211 --> 00:30:41,256
Like, menopause symptoms?

342
00:30:42,841 --> 00:30:46,428
But there's no way Yu-mi's already
going through menopause.

343
00:30:50,724 --> 00:30:51,725
Why?

344
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:54,853
What is it?

345
00:30:57,522 --> 00:31:01,109
What is it? Oh, come on!

346
00:31:26,927 --> 00:31:28,303
The light's on.

347
00:31:30,389 --> 00:31:31,723
Let's get to work, Soon-rok.

348
00:31:32,015 --> 00:31:34,017
We have a load of work to do.

349
00:31:35,227 --> 00:31:38,563
BUSAN STATION

350
00:31:58,792 --> 00:32:00,669
Ms. Kim, I'm on the train.

351
00:32:01,044 --> 00:32:02,963
I'm scheduled to arrive in 15 minutes.

352
00:32:03,463 --> 00:32:05,090
SHIN SOON-ROK PD

353
00:32:05,215 --> 00:32:07,509
I'll be waiting at Platform 9.

354
00:32:42,669 --> 00:32:45,130
How many minutes are left?

355
00:32:45,213 --> 00:32:46,548
Five minutes left.

356
00:32:46,631 --> 00:32:48,592
- That's a relief.
- Okay.

357
00:32:48,675 --> 00:32:51,470
That jerk will be here in five minutes.

358
00:32:51,887 --> 00:32:54,097
Let's not get swept up by that jerk again.

359
00:32:54,347 --> 00:32:59,019
If he smirks, fakes a call,
and pulls his usual stunt

360
00:32:59,769 --> 00:33:01,855
we're not letting him get away with it.

361
00:33:02,189 --> 00:33:03,648
We have to crush him.

362
00:33:04,065 --> 00:33:05,901
We have to destroy him.

363
00:33:14,117 --> 00:33:17,287
- How many minutes left?
- One minute left.

364
00:33:17,537 --> 00:33:18,705
He's almost here.

365
00:33:20,290 --> 00:33:22,584
The train is now arriving.

366
00:33:25,337 --> 00:33:28,548
- He's finally coming!
- Let's crush him.

367
00:33:28,632 --> 00:33:30,383
Let's destroy him!

368
00:33:42,687 --> 00:33:44,064
Where is that jerk?

369
00:33:44,981 --> 00:33:46,525
Huh? I don't see him.

370
00:33:47,442 --> 00:33:48,485
Did he ditch us again?

371
00:33:49,194 --> 00:33:51,279
If he ditched us again, I swear...

372
00:33:57,536 --> 00:33:59,996
- There he is!
- That jerk showed up!

373
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:01,748
That son of a bitch!

374
00:34:02,791 --> 00:34:03,792
- What's that?
- What's that?

375
00:35:18,366 --> 00:35:19,868
Ms. Kim, I'm sorry.

376
00:35:20,285 --> 00:35:21,786
I made such a ridiculous mistake...

377
00:35:22,579 --> 00:35:24,706
I got off for a moment
and was about to get back on...

378
00:35:24,789 --> 00:35:25,832
I'm sorry.

379
00:35:26,916 --> 00:35:28,418
Right, well...

380
00:35:28,543 --> 00:35:32,005
They said they'd send a car,
but it hasn't arrived yet.

381
00:35:32,589 --> 00:35:35,842
But I'm glad we seem
to have some time to spare.

382
00:35:36,259 --> 00:35:37,594
We should probably head out now.

383
00:35:39,054 --> 00:35:40,138
Oh, and...

384
00:35:41,097 --> 00:35:44,517
I couldn't answer you earlier

385
00:35:45,268 --> 00:35:46,811
but it really was because of my schedule.

386
00:35:47,103 --> 00:35:48,938
There was no other reason.

387
00:35:49,397 --> 00:35:51,941
If you misunderstood, I apologize.

388
00:35:58,490 --> 00:35:59,532
Look.

389
00:36:00,075 --> 00:36:01,701
Love is gone.

390
00:36:02,619 --> 00:36:04,496
Love woke up?

391
00:36:04,579 --> 00:36:05,580
Why?

392
00:36:05,955 --> 00:36:07,082
I don't know.

393
00:36:07,165 --> 00:36:08,750
Where did Love go?

394
00:36:09,125 --> 00:36:10,835
LOVE CELL

395
00:36:10,919 --> 00:36:12,212
Wait a minute.

396
00:36:12,379 --> 00:36:14,005
Then that lightning bolt...

397
00:36:17,217 --> 00:36:18,218
Let's go.

398
00:36:37,570 --> 00:36:40,448
This is the kind of scene
you'd only see in Yu-mi's novels.

399
00:36:41,408 --> 00:36:42,534
Is this for real?

400
00:36:45,704 --> 00:36:49,124
Can you really fall for someone
in a flash like that?

401
00:36:49,958 --> 00:36:50,959
GONG FOR PUBLIC, SA FOR PRIVATE.

402
00:36:51,042 --> 00:36:54,879
EPISODE 9
PUBLIC AND PRIVATE LIVES

403
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:57,549
All right, next up is
the author of a hit novel.

404
00:36:57,632 --> 00:37:00,844
Please welcome Kim Yu-mi, author of
Sincerity Smells Like Oranges

405
00:37:00,927 --> 00:37:05,223
HAEUNDAE BADAMUN ART HALL
20TH ANNIVERSARY BOOK TALK

406
00:37:08,601 --> 00:37:11,980
Yes, hello. I'm writer Kim Yu-mi.

407
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:15,400
All right, we'll now begin
the Q&amp;A session.

408
00:37:15,483 --> 00:37:17,068
A question for writer Kim Yu-mi...

409
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:24,492
Actually, being a writer was just
a vague childhood dream of mine.

410
00:37:25,493 --> 00:37:27,454
Now that I'm older...

411
00:37:27,704 --> 00:37:30,457
It was a short but enjoyable time.

412
00:37:30,540 --> 00:37:34,461
I'll be back with another great book.
Thank you.

413
00:37:37,088 --> 00:37:39,966
- Ms. Kim, I'm a fan.
- Thank you.

414
00:37:41,885 --> 00:37:42,927
Please smile.

415
00:37:45,305 --> 00:37:47,515
- What's your name?
- Jin Hui-jeong.

416
00:37:47,599 --> 00:37:48,641
Jin Hui-jeong...

417
00:37:51,686 --> 00:37:53,897
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

418
00:38:03,990 --> 00:38:06,576
Ms. Kim, all your photos came out great.

419
00:38:07,952 --> 00:38:09,871
You got a bouquet too?

420
00:38:10,997 --> 00:38:12,874
Ms. Kim, you're a total superstar!

421
00:38:14,083 --> 00:38:15,126
How pretty.

422
00:38:16,085 --> 00:38:18,713
- Here's the cake you ordered.
- Okay.

423
00:38:21,424 --> 00:38:23,510
- Thank you.
- Have a good one.

424
00:38:35,772 --> 00:38:38,483
Ms. Kim, I'm here.

425
00:38:39,192 --> 00:38:40,235
Oh, you're here?

426
00:38:41,861 --> 00:38:43,571
Did you have a good trip to Busan?

427
00:38:46,157 --> 00:38:47,200
Yeah.

428
00:38:48,076 --> 00:38:52,497
I saw your blog's Book Talk photos.
So many people came!

429
00:38:52,789 --> 00:38:55,416
Yeah. More people came than I expected.

430
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:58,253
See? I told you you have a ton of fans.

431
00:38:58,962 --> 00:39:00,129
That's not it.

432
00:39:00,505 --> 00:39:02,048
There were several guest writers.

433
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:07,262
But Ms. Kim, you seem very calm today.

434
00:39:09,597 --> 00:39:13,142
- I do?
- Yes. You seem unusually calm.

435
00:39:14,435 --> 00:39:16,062
There's nothing to get excited about.

436
00:39:16,729 --> 00:39:17,897
It's the same every day.

437
00:39:18,898 --> 00:39:19,941
Is that so?

438
00:39:25,154 --> 00:39:26,823
Calm, my ass.

439
00:39:27,824 --> 00:39:29,659
She has no idea

440
00:39:29,742 --> 00:39:33,371
but the village is a complete wreck!

441
00:39:39,669 --> 00:39:42,839
Just look at the state of the village
these past few days.

442
00:39:43,673 --> 00:39:45,133
But I can't let it show.

443
00:39:45,341 --> 00:39:47,719
If I look calm, I've succeeded.

444
00:39:49,721 --> 00:39:50,889
- Should we go to the hospital?
- Yeah.

445
00:39:54,309 --> 00:39:58,271
They have symptoms of partial memory loss
after being struck by lightning.

446
00:39:59,147 --> 00:40:01,649
Partial memory loss?

447
00:40:02,358 --> 00:40:05,069
When he took off his glasses
and let his hair down,

448
00:40:05,612 --> 00:40:08,114
Soon-rok looked like a puppy.

449
00:40:09,115 --> 00:40:12,243
And when he smiled, it was incredible.

450
00:40:13,244 --> 00:40:14,662
So cute!

451
00:40:14,954 --> 00:40:16,706
- Right!
- Right!

452
00:40:17,749 --> 00:40:19,375
- What was that?
- But you guys were

453
00:40:19,459 --> 00:40:22,670
furious with Soon-rok. Don't you remember?

454
00:40:24,255 --> 00:40:25,715
Oh, were we?

455
00:40:26,257 --> 00:40:28,259
Right, I think we were angry.

456
00:40:28,343 --> 00:40:31,220
But why were we angry?

457
00:40:31,304 --> 00:40:33,056
Soon-rok...

458
00:40:33,723 --> 00:40:35,266
Because he was leaving?

459
00:40:36,684 --> 00:40:38,311
- That's right!
- That's right!

460
00:40:38,394 --> 00:40:40,229
- I think that was it.
- I think that was it.

461
00:40:46,194 --> 00:40:48,321
Love disappeared.

462
00:40:50,657 --> 00:40:51,824
Naughty Cell also.

463
00:40:53,910 --> 00:40:55,870
Man-Patrol Squad.

464
00:40:56,329 --> 00:40:58,039
Tongue Cell disappeared, too.

465
00:40:59,582 --> 00:41:01,501
Why did Naughty and Tongue Cells wake up?

466
00:41:01,584 --> 00:41:03,086
She doesn't even have a boyfriend!

467
00:41:03,336 --> 00:41:05,046
What are they going to do
now that they're awake?

468
00:41:05,129 --> 00:41:07,006
Those useless things!

469
00:41:07,298 --> 00:41:09,258
They only woke up because of the lightning

470
00:41:09,342 --> 00:41:12,303
so I don't think they woke up
for a specific reason.

471
00:41:12,387 --> 00:41:15,890
Hurry and find them all!
Before they run wild again!

472
00:41:16,182 --> 00:41:18,059
Without them, I...

473
00:41:18,142 --> 00:41:21,104
No, Yu-mi was so at peace!

474
00:41:25,274 --> 00:41:28,361
It just glitched from the lightning.
It's no big deal.

475
00:41:28,444 --> 00:41:30,780
Everything will be back to normal soon.

476
00:41:30,905 --> 00:41:32,907
It's not like we'll see
Shin Soon-rok anymore anyway.

477
00:41:33,449 --> 00:41:34,492
That's true.

478
00:41:37,328 --> 00:41:40,081
In a few days,
it'll be as if nothing happened.

479
00:41:47,630 --> 00:41:48,631
Let's start the meeting.

480
00:41:50,341 --> 00:41:53,261
- What's this? A cake?
- Yes, a birthday cake.

481
00:41:53,761 --> 00:41:54,887
A birthday cake?

482
00:41:55,013 --> 00:41:58,433
I didn't know,
but today is Shin PD's birthday.

483
00:41:59,100 --> 00:42:02,562
I set a reminder on my messenger,
and it popped up this morning.

484
00:42:02,895 --> 00:42:04,939
It works out perfectly
since we have a meeting today.

485
00:42:06,941 --> 00:42:09,652
It's pretty, right? It's a low-sugar cake.

486
00:42:10,194 --> 00:42:11,821
I guess I forgot to tell you.

487
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:13,781
Shin PD isn't coming today.

488
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:17,785
- Why?
- He's off our team starting today.

489
00:42:18,202 --> 00:42:20,163
- What?
- Last week was his last.

490
00:42:20,413 --> 00:42:23,666
- I forgot to tell you.
- But, why?

491
00:42:24,125 --> 00:42:26,502
He said his schedule was a mess
since he was managing too many teams.

492
00:42:27,336 --> 00:42:29,547
Let's eat the cake ourselves.
It looks delicious.

493
00:42:30,590 --> 00:42:33,593
I'm so disappointed.
This is a major disappointment.

494
00:42:34,761 --> 00:42:36,262
Come on,
how is it a "major disappointment"?

495
00:42:36,554 --> 00:42:38,222
I liked Shin PD.

496
00:42:38,389 --> 00:42:40,058
Did you come to the meeting
for personal reasons?

497
00:42:41,517 --> 00:42:43,186
We're not even having a farewell party?

498
00:42:43,269 --> 00:42:47,523
- Let's at least have a team dinner.
- A party? We only met a few times.

499
00:42:47,774 --> 00:42:49,317
It's his birthday.

500
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:51,194
Let's have a farewell and birthday party.

501
00:42:51,819 --> 00:42:53,738
He won't be coming here anymore.

502
00:42:57,033 --> 00:43:00,203
If you're that disappointed,
wish him happy birthday yourself.

503
00:43:01,412 --> 00:43:02,413
I guess I should.

504
00:43:08,711 --> 00:43:09,712
I sent it.

505
00:43:10,505 --> 00:43:11,964
You sent him a happy birthday message?

506
00:43:12,131 --> 00:43:15,093
I said I'm very sad
that he quit so suddenly.

507
00:43:16,052 --> 00:43:19,180
I never knew you liked him so much.

508
00:43:19,347 --> 00:43:21,099
He was surprisingly cute.

509
00:43:21,265 --> 00:43:23,768
He looks just like a puppy
without his glasses.

510
00:43:25,686 --> 00:43:28,481
He took off his glasses
for a moment the other day

511
00:43:29,857 --> 00:43:31,859
and he was so cute.

512
00:43:32,026 --> 00:43:35,988
So I told him to wear contacts.
And do you know what he said?

513
00:43:38,825 --> 00:43:39,826
What did he say?

514
00:43:43,204 --> 00:43:44,622
I wear them to look cold.

515
00:43:45,957 --> 00:43:47,083
What does that mean?

516
00:43:48,042 --> 00:43:50,545
He said he wants to look cold.

517
00:43:50,628 --> 00:43:53,131
So that people won't bother him.

518
00:43:53,548 --> 00:43:55,883
He's so cute and funny.

519
00:43:57,301 --> 00:43:58,344
It's Shin PD.

520
00:44:00,096 --> 00:44:03,015
Hello? Oh, hello.

521
00:44:04,225 --> 00:44:07,436
Yes, I'm at the meeting now,
and I heard from Ms. Kim.

522
00:44:08,813 --> 00:44:10,273
Yes, at her studio.

523
00:44:11,149 --> 00:44:12,400
Oh, really?

524
00:44:13,442 --> 00:44:15,987
Yes, okay. Bye.

525
00:44:19,282 --> 00:44:21,117
Shin PD is nearby right now.

526
00:44:22,326 --> 00:44:24,662
- Really?
- He said he'll stop by for a bit.

527
00:44:24,745 --> 00:44:27,081
- Now? He's coming here?
- Yes.

528
00:44:27,540 --> 00:44:30,251
He asked if he could come up,
so I told him to.

529
00:44:30,835 --> 00:44:34,547
That's great.
We'll cut the cake when he's here.

530
00:44:35,131 --> 00:44:36,591
Let's surprise him.

531
00:44:40,052 --> 00:44:42,180
What? Things were just calming down.

532
00:44:42,597 --> 00:44:44,182
Why is he coming?

533
00:44:44,599 --> 00:44:46,601
-Thump, thump, thump, thump.
-What's this sound?

534
00:44:46,684 --> 00:44:48,853
- Thump, thump, thump, thump.
- Thump, thump, thump, thump.

535
00:44:48,936 --> 00:44:54,901
- Thump, thump, thump, thump.
- Thump, thump, thump, thump.

536
00:44:54,984 --> 00:44:58,070
- Thump, thump, thump, thump.
- Hey, Koongsimi! Kwangsimi!

537
00:44:58,279 --> 00:45:01,782
- Why are you two beating the drums?
- Thump, thump, thump, thump.

538
00:45:02,033 --> 00:45:04,243
- Thump, thump, thump, thump
- Thump, thump, thump, thump

539
00:45:04,493 --> 00:45:06,871
Why is your heart suddenly pounding?

540
00:45:07,246 --> 00:45:10,666
- Ms. Kim, I'll put this away for now.
- Okay.

541
00:45:21,969 --> 00:45:23,221
He's unbelievable.

542
00:45:24,263 --> 00:45:26,224
He quit when he wanted.
Why is he suddenly back?

543
00:45:39,737 --> 00:45:41,489
- He's here.
- Okay.

544
00:45:43,407 --> 00:45:46,160
Ms. Kim, can I put some on too?

545
00:45:47,453 --> 00:45:50,456
- Put on what?
- Lip gloss. I didn't bring mine.

546
00:45:52,833 --> 00:45:54,043
Didn't you just put on some?

547
00:45:55,878 --> 00:45:57,713
Well, yeah...

548
00:45:58,631 --> 00:46:00,424
My lips keep getting chapped.

549
00:46:09,517 --> 00:46:11,269
I like that it has color.

550
00:46:14,563 --> 00:46:15,564
Hey!

551
00:46:17,775 --> 00:46:20,945
Why the sudden lip gloss? Huh?

552
00:46:21,946 --> 00:46:22,989
I told you.

553
00:46:24,073 --> 00:46:25,700
My lips are chapped.

554
00:46:27,493 --> 00:46:29,370
- Hello.
- Hello.

555
00:46:29,954 --> 00:46:32,123
Ms. Kim, Shin PD is here.

556
00:46:42,633 --> 00:46:47,096
- Thump, thump, thump, thump
- Thump, thump, thump, thump

557
00:46:47,179 --> 00:46:50,349
- Thump, thump, thump.
- Thump, thump, thump.

558
00:46:51,142 --> 00:46:54,145
- Thump, thump, thump.
- What? Why is this happening again?

559
00:46:54,270 --> 00:46:56,647
Exactly! Why is this happening again?

560
00:46:56,731 --> 00:47:00,818
- Thump, thump, thump, thump
- Thump, thump, thump, thump

561
00:47:00,901 --> 00:47:02,570
Ms. Kim, hello.

562
00:47:09,410 --> 00:47:10,411
You came.

563
00:47:15,750 --> 00:47:17,752
Did you rest well after Busan?

564
00:47:18,127 --> 00:47:19,253
Yeah, sort of.

565
00:47:19,420 --> 00:47:22,381
- But how...
- I had something to do nearby.

566
00:47:22,840 --> 00:47:26,594
I was going to stop by anyway,
and Na-hee contacted me.

567
00:47:27,303 --> 00:47:28,304
I see.

568
00:47:29,221 --> 00:47:30,431
I came to give you this.

569
00:47:31,807 --> 00:47:32,808
What's this?

570
00:47:33,142 --> 00:47:36,854
The Book Talk organizers
sent you some high-res photos.

571
00:47:37,438 --> 00:47:39,315
I picked a good one and had it framed.

572
00:47:41,317 --> 00:47:42,568
You look pretty in it.

573
00:47:46,155 --> 00:47:49,617
You shouldn't have. Thank you.

574
00:47:52,036 --> 00:47:53,204
Ta-da!

575
00:47:54,830 --> 00:47:56,999
Happy birthday, Shin PD!

576
00:47:57,541 --> 00:47:58,626
It's your birthday today, right?

577
00:48:00,086 --> 00:48:02,797
- How did you know?
- I just knew.

578
00:48:03,047 --> 00:48:04,298
How did you know?

579
00:48:05,091 --> 00:48:07,051
Na-hee is quick with these things.

580
00:48:07,551 --> 00:48:10,638
- Okay, let's sing the birthday song.
- No, that's okay.

581
00:48:10,721 --> 00:48:12,139
Ms. Kim, let's start.

582
00:48:12,348 --> 00:48:15,684
Happy birthday to you

583
00:48:15,935 --> 00:48:19,647
- Happy birthday to you
- Wait!

584
00:48:20,022 --> 00:48:21,315
...to you

585
00:48:22,108 --> 00:48:26,195
I have to say "dear" next.
To Shin Soon-rok!

586
00:48:26,278 --> 00:48:30,241
It's a song you sing even to an enemy
on their birthday. What's so weird?

587
00:48:30,574 --> 00:48:34,203
No, but still, to Shin Soon-rok...

588
00:48:36,205 --> 00:48:39,667
Happy birthday to you

589
00:48:39,917 --> 00:48:43,546
Happy birthday, dear Shin PD

590
00:48:43,963 --> 00:48:47,216
Happy birthday to you

591
00:48:48,509 --> 00:48:51,720
Is Yu-mi blushing? But why?

592
00:48:53,055 --> 00:48:55,099
- Blow them out.
- Okay.

593
00:48:58,477 --> 00:48:59,895
Happy birthday.

594
00:48:59,979 --> 00:49:01,647
- Happy birthday.
- Thank you.

595
00:49:02,982 --> 00:49:04,233
I'm so flustered.

596
00:49:05,401 --> 00:49:08,112
Have some cake before you go.

597
00:49:09,113 --> 00:49:11,740
- Yes, have a seat here.
- Okay.

598
00:49:12,992 --> 00:49:15,870
- Ms. Kim, I'll get it.
- It's okay. I'll do it.

599
00:49:15,953 --> 00:49:17,413
- You can cut the cake.
- Oh, okay.

600
00:49:25,171 --> 00:49:27,214
I bought the right number
of candles, right?

601
00:49:27,339 --> 00:49:32,178
- Your 30th birthday.
- What? Shin PD is only 30?

602
00:49:32,511 --> 00:49:35,681
- No. I'm not 30.
- I knew it.

603
00:49:35,931 --> 00:49:38,017
We must be only a year or two apart.

604
00:49:38,225 --> 00:49:40,352
To be exact, I'm 29.

605
00:49:42,396 --> 00:49:43,481
Really?

606
00:49:43,772 --> 00:49:47,193
- Then we're only one year apart.
- Yes.

607
00:49:47,985 --> 00:49:50,738
That's crazy. He's in his twenties?

608
00:49:51,780 --> 00:49:55,951
No, then what's the age difference
between him and Yu-mi?

609
00:49:56,118 --> 00:50:00,039
- One, two.
- Why are you counting? Huh?

610
00:50:00,789 --> 00:50:03,000
- What use will that information have?
- It hurts!

611
00:50:07,713 --> 00:50:09,381
I'm going to make some coffee.

612
00:50:09,840 --> 00:50:10,841
Anyone want some?

613
00:50:11,383 --> 00:50:13,761
Can I get an iced Americano then?

614
00:50:14,178 --> 00:50:15,471
- Of course.
- Thank you.

615
00:50:15,554 --> 00:50:17,223
- I'll do it.
- No, it's okay.

616
00:50:17,848 --> 00:50:19,099
- You too, right?
- Yes.

617
00:50:21,769 --> 00:50:23,646
Shin PD, did you have your birthday soup?

618
00:50:24,563 --> 00:50:26,982
- No.
- Why not? Do you live alone?

619
00:50:27,816 --> 00:50:30,236
Yes. I moved out during college.

620
00:50:30,986 --> 00:50:32,488
He lives alone?

621
00:50:32,988 --> 00:50:34,073
What about your parents?

622
00:50:35,032 --> 00:50:38,619
My parents retired, built a house
in the country, and moved.

623
00:50:38,827 --> 00:50:41,997
- To Yangpyeong.
- So you go visit them every weekend?

624
00:50:42,456 --> 00:50:43,541
I go sometimes.

625
00:50:43,624 --> 00:50:45,167
I need to rest at home on the weekends.

626
00:50:46,210 --> 00:50:50,172
- So you're a homebody, Shin PD.
- I'm a total homebody.

627
00:50:53,217 --> 00:50:54,718
Oh, he's a homebody?

628
00:50:55,052 --> 00:50:57,805
- He's just like me.
- Any plans for your birthday?

629
00:50:58,514 --> 00:50:59,515
Perhaps a date?

630
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:04,270
Who would I go on a date with?

631
00:51:05,312 --> 00:51:06,564
That was a good question.

632
00:51:06,981 --> 00:51:08,816
Soon-rok doesn't have a girlfriend.

633
00:51:09,984 --> 00:51:11,235
So?

634
00:51:16,907 --> 00:51:18,867
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

635
00:51:21,328 --> 00:51:22,454
I'll enjoy it.

636
00:51:31,797 --> 00:51:32,881
The coffee is delicious.

637
00:51:34,341 --> 00:51:37,886
- The coffee is smooth, right?
- Yes. And the cake is delicious too.

638
00:51:38,345 --> 00:51:39,430
Thank you.

639
00:51:40,347 --> 00:51:42,850
I didn't buy it. Na-hee did.

640
00:51:44,143 --> 00:51:46,562
- I bought it.
- The cake is delicious.

641
00:51:47,646 --> 00:51:51,817
But, Shin PD, this is the most
I've ever seen you talk.

642
00:51:54,361 --> 00:51:56,488
- Really?
- Right, Ms. Kim?

643
00:51:56,947 --> 00:51:57,948
That's right.

644
00:51:59,575 --> 00:52:01,327
It must be because I'm not here for work.

645
00:52:01,619 --> 00:52:03,245
I feel more relaxed.

646
00:52:03,495 --> 00:52:05,914
So you've felt uncomfortable
coming here until now?

647
00:52:06,582 --> 00:52:07,583
I'm the type

648
00:52:07,833 --> 00:52:10,377
who's very strict about
separating work and my private life

649
00:52:10,461 --> 00:52:13,255
so it just happens
without me realizing it.

650
00:52:15,132 --> 00:52:16,592
It's not a good personality trait.

651
00:52:16,884 --> 00:52:20,304
- Come visit outside of work sometime.
- I will.

652
00:52:20,554 --> 00:52:22,431
It's your birthday.
What are you doing this evening?

653
00:52:22,598 --> 00:52:24,892
- If you're not going on a date?
- I'm going to Busan.

654
00:52:25,184 --> 00:52:26,685
- Busan again?
- Yes.

655
00:52:26,769 --> 00:52:28,145
We're having a publisher's workshop.

656
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:30,314
It's for four days,
and all the writers are going too.

657
00:52:31,231 --> 00:52:34,526
I heard you weren't going
because of the Busan business trip.

658
00:52:35,444 --> 00:52:37,655
Oh, yes, that's right.

659
00:52:38,280 --> 00:52:40,240
Because I didn't want to go again
just two days later.

660
00:52:40,324 --> 00:52:42,826
And I'm going again just two days later.

661
00:52:45,621 --> 00:52:47,790
That must be tough,
especially on your birthday.

662
00:52:51,085 --> 00:52:52,878
Well, I'll be on my way.

663
00:52:53,545 --> 00:52:55,339
Happy birthday.

664
00:52:56,924 --> 00:52:57,925
Thank you.

665
00:53:06,475 --> 00:53:08,435
- Goodbye.
- Take care.

666
00:53:13,565 --> 00:53:15,484
Why did I say
I wasn't going to the workshop?

667
00:53:15,609 --> 00:53:17,403
- Everyone is going.
- Hey.

668
00:53:17,903 --> 00:53:21,031
Waste a week when I have to write?

669
00:53:21,407 --> 00:53:22,616
But Soon-rok is going...

670
00:53:23,784 --> 00:53:24,785
So?

671
00:53:25,202 --> 00:53:28,038
- I'm just saying.
- Hey! Why are you like this too?

672
00:53:28,247 --> 00:53:30,624
You're Rational Cell. Get a grip!

673
00:53:30,708 --> 00:53:34,336
- The workshop isn't bad for work.
- It is bad.

674
00:53:35,713 --> 00:53:36,755
I said it's bad!

675
00:53:37,840 --> 00:53:40,509
Especially! Now! Even more so!

676
00:53:43,345 --> 00:53:45,597
Shut up and let me just write.

677
00:53:49,101 --> 00:53:53,480
Then what if the Maltese disappears
while she's taking out the trash?

678
00:53:53,772 --> 00:53:57,234
The Maltese goes out the open door,
gets on the elevator, and disappears.

679
00:53:57,484 --> 00:54:00,988
The male lead finds out and is
furious with the female lead...

680
00:54:03,490 --> 00:54:05,826
That's a good idea too.

681
00:54:05,993 --> 00:54:10,789
Or, she finds the Maltese is sick,
and she takes it to the vet.

682
00:54:10,873 --> 00:54:13,751
But her phone died...

683
00:54:17,212 --> 00:54:19,423
- She looks for the Maltese...
- That's also...

684
00:54:20,632 --> 00:54:21,675
good.

685
00:54:23,218 --> 00:54:25,596
- But, you know, Na-hee.
- Yes?

686
00:54:26,180 --> 00:54:28,932
Should we end our meeting
a little early today?

687
00:54:29,433 --> 00:54:33,270
- Sorry?
- Something came up.

688
00:54:33,729 --> 00:54:36,356
How about we wrap up today
and meet online tomorrow?

689
00:54:36,523 --> 00:54:39,276
That last idea was good.
I think we can finish up quickly.

690
00:54:39,735 --> 00:54:40,736
Okay.

691
00:54:41,737 --> 00:54:43,197
You're an idea bank.

692
00:54:46,366 --> 00:54:48,702
Why, why is she like this?
Why is she being like this again?

693
00:54:49,453 --> 00:54:52,122
We only started the meeting
a little while ago!

694
00:54:52,206 --> 00:54:53,957
Don't you know why she's acting like this?

695
00:54:58,629 --> 00:55:01,673
You still don't know
why Yu-mi is acting like this?

696
00:55:02,716 --> 00:55:05,511
Love! Where were you hiding?

697
00:55:06,011 --> 00:55:08,263
She's here! Get her!

698
00:55:15,729 --> 00:55:16,730
You fools!

699
00:55:17,731 --> 00:55:20,943
How can someone in love be calm?

700
00:55:21,527 --> 00:55:23,362
Wha... what are you talking about?

701
00:55:23,695 --> 00:55:25,656
The world has changed, Writer Cell.

702
00:55:25,989 --> 00:55:29,076
The moment lightning struck,
Yu-mi changed.

703
00:55:33,205 --> 00:55:34,623
Hello? Ms. Kim!

704
00:55:35,499 --> 00:55:36,708
Jang PD.

705
00:55:37,292 --> 00:55:38,752
Are you in Busan?

706
00:55:39,211 --> 00:55:41,839
Yes, I came down this morning
with the Chief Editor.

707
00:55:43,757 --> 00:55:47,678
I'm thinking of going to Busan, too.
Are there any rooms available?

708
00:55:48,387 --> 00:55:49,763
Gosh, you're coming?

709
00:55:50,514 --> 00:55:54,852
Yes, well, it's not often
I get to see all the writers

710
00:55:54,935 --> 00:55:56,895
so I figured I should go.

711
00:55:57,688 --> 00:55:59,648
Of course, we'd love for you to come.

712
00:55:59,731 --> 00:56:00,899
Please come.

713
00:56:01,817 --> 00:56:05,279
- Okay, I'll take the evening train.
- Okay.

714
00:56:05,737 --> 00:56:07,239
The Chief Editor will be happy.

715
00:56:07,322 --> 00:56:10,367
- Hurry and come down.
- Okay, I'll call you when I arrive.

716
00:56:10,868 --> 00:56:11,869
Okay.

717
00:56:14,830 --> 00:56:16,540
I'm crazy. I'm crazy.

718
00:56:20,669 --> 00:56:24,256
- I'm reclaiming my Prime Cell spot.
- What?

719
00:56:24,548 --> 00:56:27,384
And you'd better hand over
this castle, too.

720
00:56:27,885 --> 00:56:31,263
That's crazy. Hey!
Who said you could be the Prime Cell?

721
00:56:31,346 --> 00:56:33,390
Hey, what are you doing? Get her now!

722
00:57:12,804 --> 00:57:15,098
What do you think you're doing,
Kim Yu-mi, huh?

723
00:57:16,642 --> 00:57:19,478
What are you doing? Seriously.
You're crazy!

724
00:57:28,278 --> 00:57:29,821
You're really crazy.

725
00:57:29,905 --> 00:57:31,698
You can't separate your personal
and professional lives.

726
00:57:32,616 --> 00:57:35,035
Unlike someone who's so strict about it.

727
00:57:35,535 --> 00:57:36,787
I'm crazy. I'm crazy.

728
00:58:01,478 --> 00:58:03,271
SEOUL METROPOLITAN CITY

729
00:58:07,693 --> 00:58:09,528
How old are you?

730
00:58:09,945 --> 00:58:12,364
- You must be crazy...
- Excuse me?

731
00:58:13,365 --> 00:58:14,408
It's nothing.

732
00:58:16,493 --> 00:58:18,245
I'm crazy. I'm crazy.

733
00:58:28,296 --> 00:58:29,631
Hello, Jang PD.

734
00:58:29,881 --> 00:58:32,134
Ms. Kim, you aren't
on the train yet, right?

735
00:58:33,051 --> 00:58:37,180
- I was about to buy my ticket...
- Oh, that's great.

736
00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:40,392
Shin PD is on his way down.
He's still at the station.

737
00:58:41,893 --> 00:58:44,813
- What?
- How about coming down with Shin PD?

738
00:58:44,980 --> 00:58:46,148
I'll tell him to get you a seat.

739
00:58:47,566 --> 00:58:48,608
Okay.

740
00:59:04,416 --> 00:59:05,876
This is seriously crazy.

741
00:59:06,334 --> 00:59:08,670
Why am I so nervous? It's not a big deal.

742
00:59:13,091 --> 00:59:14,092
Ms. Kim.

743
00:59:48,168 --> 00:59:54,925
A CRUSH HAS BEGUN

744
01:00:01,181 --> 01:00:03,225
Fine, I admit it.

745
01:00:04,351 --> 01:00:05,352
I...

746
01:00:06,436 --> 01:00:09,022
like Soon-rok.

747
01:00:13,819 --> 01:00:14,820
Hey.

748
01:00:15,028 --> 01:00:17,155
You think you can take my spot?

749
01:00:17,948 --> 01:00:20,075
I've been working on this for years.

750
01:00:20,283 --> 01:00:22,369
I'm still the Prime Cell!

751
01:00:25,705 --> 01:00:26,832
Bring it on.

752
01:00:27,207 --> 01:00:29,459
Let's see who the final winner will be.

753
01:00:29,835 --> 01:00:30,836
That's ridiculous.

754
01:00:31,044 --> 01:00:33,922
Shin Soon-rok isn't even
interested in Yu-mi.

755
01:00:34,214 --> 01:00:36,216
He even hates her!

756
01:00:36,633 --> 01:00:37,717
He's probably scared of her.

757
01:00:37,801 --> 01:00:42,305
After she threw a fit like that.
He has to deal with her. For work.

758
01:00:42,389 --> 01:00:43,431
Don't you get it?

759
01:00:53,108 --> 01:00:54,943
- Please take a seat.
- Thanks.

760
01:01:05,203 --> 01:01:06,955
Earlier today, you said
you weren't coming...

761
01:01:07,372 --> 01:01:08,498
Right, I did...

762
01:01:09,374 --> 01:01:10,959
but the meeting ended early.

763
01:01:11,418 --> 01:01:14,546
And Jang PD kept insisting that I come.

764
01:01:14,629 --> 01:01:15,755
Oh, I see.

765
01:01:16,715 --> 01:01:20,343
- So that's how we came together.
- The train is now departing.

766
01:01:20,427 --> 01:01:21,469
Right.

767
01:01:44,534 --> 01:01:46,453
Would you like some coffee?

768
01:01:46,661 --> 01:01:49,831
- No, thank you. I already had some.
- Okay.

769
01:02:17,275 --> 01:02:21,029
GOING HOME

770
01:02:44,177 --> 01:02:45,178
See?

771
01:02:45,512 --> 01:02:47,472
Are you going to have
a hopeless, one-sided crush?

772
01:02:47,847 --> 01:02:49,641
- I don't care.
- What?

773
01:02:50,475 --> 01:02:51,518
What's important is...

774
01:02:52,435 --> 01:02:54,187
that I have woken up.

775
01:03:07,909 --> 01:03:09,119
What's important is...

776
01:03:09,536 --> 01:03:12,706
that Yu-mi's bland daily life is over.

777
01:03:56,041 --> 01:03:57,792
A CRUSH HAS BEGUN

778
01:03:58,293 --> 01:04:00,795
YUMI'S CELLS 3

779
01:04:01,379 --> 01:04:03,923
- It's Soon-rok!
- He's so cute.

780
01:04:04,299 --> 01:04:05,800
Yu-mi, get a grip.

781
01:04:05,967 --> 01:04:07,218
This is Writer Kim Ju-ho.

782
01:04:07,302 --> 01:04:08,595
Oh, yes. It's nice to meet you.

783
01:04:08,678 --> 01:04:10,847
- Sorry, what year did you start school?
- Wait.

784
01:04:10,930 --> 01:04:12,974
Why would you suddenly ask that?

785
01:04:13,058 --> 01:04:15,435
You're sure Ms. Kim
doesn't have a boyfriend, right?

786
01:04:15,560 --> 01:04:18,063
It looks like you all plotted
to set me up with that writer.

787
01:04:18,146 --> 01:04:19,939
Don't they look good together?

788
01:04:20,148 --> 01:04:21,566
They don't look good together.

789
01:04:21,649 --> 01:04:24,277
With confidence,
let's go for flirting stage!

790
01:04:24,361 --> 01:04:26,571
- Flirting stage!
- Flirting stage!

